As a
 **Data Engineer** 
 , you will play a key role in enhancing and expanding the core of our data platform. Your work will focus on building a future\-proof solution with streamlined, efficient ETL processes. We value innovation and encourage you to stay ahead of technological advancements, integrating them into our daily operations to drive continuous improvement. Collaboration will be at the heart of your role, as you work closely with the IT Architect and Product Owner to make strategic decisions, with a strong emphasis on data quality and metadata management. Your contributions will enable high\-quality information products that empower key domains such as Finance, Operations, Management, and HR.










**Example of a project you'll work on:** 




 At Nedap, we are developing a system to trace products from production to the end customer. This involves building a data pipeline that processes and stores both structured and unstructured data in Azure Data Lake. The system aims to enable production lines to track products at every stage, identify customer\-reported issues, and analyze product lifecycles using advanced data analytics.










 As a Data Engineer, you will be instrumental in designing scalable pipelines, ensuring data quality, and recommending the best tools and architectures (e.g., Synapse Analytics, Data Factory, Databricks) to support this initiative. This project highlights the critical role you’ll play in transforming raw data into actionable insights that drive our business and enhance customer outcomes.








**Your responsibilities** 



* Take the technical lead in the ongoing development of our data platform in collaboration with the Data \& BI team;
* Provide proactive recommendations on new solutions and emerging technologies, including AI;
* Develop and maintain methodologies to ensure data quality, integrity, and consistency;
* Design and implement scalable data pipelines for processing structured and unstructured data;
* Optimize data pipelines for performance and scalability;
* Educate and inspire stakeholders on the potential of data and the capabilities of the data platform;
* Translate business needs into technological solutions and provide recommendations for solution directions.









**Your team** 




 You will be part of the Data \& BI team within Nedap's IT department. This team is responsible for unlocking data from source systems and transforming it into information products. The team consists of BI developers focussing on datasets and reports within Power BI, data engineers and a Product Owner.










 The IT department also includes Office Automation \& Business IT, with teams dedicated to infrastructure and service desk. Your team is located within the Business IT section of IT.










**Our offer** 




 As a
 **Data Engineer** 
 at Nedap, you will make a valuable contribution to our goal: making people happier and more successful in their professional lives. In addition to your salary, you are entitled to a thirteenth month, a good pension scheme, and profit sharing with the opportunity to become a shareholder of Nedap. At Nedap, everything revolves around trust and autonomy. You determine your own working hours and vacation days. We also highly value personal and professional growth. You will receive a comprehensive introduction, and we encourage you to continuously develop yourself.










 Curious about all our terms of employment? Read more here.










**Required experience and skills** 




 You are someone who takes the lead in addressing technical challenges and ensures that high\-quality solutions are implemented. You involve stakeholders throughout the process, from planning to delivering the final result. With strong analytical skills, you translate complex issues into efficient solutions. You enjoy working in a collaborative team environment where decisions are made together and results are achieved as a team.








**Besides that, you have:** 



* A university\-level working and thinking ability, preferably in the field of Business \& Information Technology, Computer Science, Data Science, or a related discipline;
* At least 5 years' experience as a Data Engineer within a dynamic environment;
* Experience with Cloud platforms (Azure) and you are familiar with data technologies (Microsoft Fabric) in a Cloud environment;
* Knowledge of database systems and you are skilled in data modelling and schema design;
* Proficient in programming languages such as Python and/or Java and query languages such as SQL;
* Experience with Power BI (preferred).

Studocu was founded on the principle that equal access to study notes reduces inequality between students. Today, we make it easy for more than 45\+ million students to share notes every month and use cutting\-edge AI learning tools (like Quizzes, AI Chat, and Ask\-AI) to help them ace their study goals. The product was a rocket ship from day one and has shown strong product\-market fit on every continent with enviable YoY growth, making us a key player in the exploding EdTech space.


Your day starts with ensuring smooth People Operations—maybe you're refining onboarding workflows to create a seamless experience for new hires or coordinating with hiring managers to streamline recruitment processes. Midday, you’re focused on employee engagement, supporting initiatives like internal communications, feedback programs, or culture\-building activities. In the afternoon, you're collaborating with managers on hiring needs, scheduling interviews, and ensuring a positive candidate experience. You might also be reviewing HR policies, maintaining data accuracy in our HR systems, or supporting team development initiatives. You wrap up the day by analysing key people metrics and providing insights to improve processes and enhance the overall employee experience.


But don’t worry! Your People team of 6 is there if you need help or advice on a specific topic from either the People Operations Specialist, Talent Partner, People Business Partner or Events \& Community Manager.

 **What you’ll be doing here:**

* **Employee Lifecycle Management** – Supporting onboarding, offboarding, and contract administration to ensure a smooth employee experience;
* **Compliance \& Payroll** – Supporting payroll processes, ensuring compliance with Dutch labor laws, supporting IND \& 30% ruling cases, parental leave policies, and handling sickness \& UWV cases;
* **Recruitment** – Collaborating with Talent Acquisition to coordinate interviews, manage candidate communication, and track hiring progress;
* **Employee Experience \& Engagement** – Contributing to initiatives enhancing employee engagement and improving internal People processes;
* **People Advisory Support** – Assisting in People \& Culture projects, providing operational support and People advisory;
* **People Systems \& Data Management** – Working together with our People Ops Specialist to maintain accurate HRIS data for reporting and analysis;
* **People Analytics** – Analyzing People data and developing future\-proof reports to support business leaders with insights;
* **Diversity, Equity \& Inclusion (DE\&I)** – Tracking and reporting DE\&I metrics while driving initiatives to foster an inclusive workplace.
* 2\+ years of relevant working experience in People \& Culture/HR, in a fast\-paced, scaling environment;
* Strong organizational skills and attention to detail;
* Experience with HR tools \& analytics to improve efficiency;
* Knowledge of HR compliance, payroll, and Dutch labor laws;
* Fluent in English, and Dutch knowledge is highly preferred;
* A proactive mindset with a hands\-on approach.

**Why you’ll love it here:**

* **Make a Real Impact:** Play a key role in shaping and improving People Operations, directly influencing Studocu’s growth and employee experience;
* **Build and Innovate:** We have a solid foundation and you’ll have the freedom to refine and enhance processes, creating a top\-tier People function;
* **Be a Culture Champion:** Help foster a people\-first, engaging, and inclusive work environment where employees thrive;
* **Collaborate and Grow:** Work closely with a passionate and supportive team that values innovation, learning, and personal development.

Role Description:
**About Us:** At Booking.com, data drives our decisions. Technology is at our core. And innovation is everywhere. But our company is more than datasets, lines of code or A/B tests. We’re the thrill of the first night in a new place. The excitement of the next morning. The friends you encounter. The journeys you take. The sights you see. And the memories you make. Through our products, partners and people, we make it easier for everyone to experience the world.



The Booking.com FP\&A team is expanding and has exciting career opportunities opening up in several teams and across different levels. Below is a general description of job responsibilities of a Junior Business Controller at Booking.com:

 **Role Description:**


In this role you will be part of a dynamic, international and fast\-paced team, working in the scope of the Enabling Functions (Finance, Strategy, LPA and People) department and part of the dynamic and fast\-paced Financial Planning and Analysis (FP\&A) team, whereby there is a clear emphasis on bridging innovative business strategies into solid financial plans. You will also be involved in reporting and explaining variances versus budget and forecast. Ad\-hoc analyses are part of the scope whenever there is a need from the business.



Secondly, you will also work on enhancing processes within our team. Think about standardizing/automating financial reporting or strengthening planning \& control processes with other departments like Accounting or Procurement.



Lastly, you will also work on Booking.com broad cost optimization projects. You will be involved in all stages of these projects, from development to execution, in close cooperation with other Business Controllers, the Business, and relevant teams outside of FP\&A.

 **Key Job Responsibilities and Duties:**

* + Support both the short and long\-term business planning process to create solid financial plans for key enabling function departments;
	+ Work with accounting and business teams on month\-end close to accurately report business results and provide insightful explanatory commentary;
	+ Provide reporting in an insightful and actionable way to the departmental leadership, including business performance presentations for all close and planning cycles;
	+ Proactively deliver intelligence based on data and support and advise your business partners on identified opportunities;
	+ Perform ad\-hoc analysis, scenarios and benchmarking as needed and contribute to new business/expansion/cost control projects and process improvement as needed;
	+ Continuously seek ways to simplify and enhance our planning and control processes;
	+ Understand what drives (financial) success for the different sub departments and develop measures for these drivers.
	+ Work closely with procurement on contract approval and savings validation process for enabling functions.

