Ayvens is looking for a new colleague who can fill the position of Senior Risk Model Developer Pillar 2 at their Amsterdam based Headoffice. The Model Developer Pillar 2 works within a team on the development, implementation and monitoring of regulatory and business models. The role also supports the risk department by analysing data in order to detect portfolio trends which cause significant changes in capital or are not within the risk appetite.










 The ideal candidate is working with an outperforming drive and has an analysing and problem\-solving mentality. You are responsible for:










**Model Development:** 



* Managing the model development projects and ensuring delivery of the model within the agreed timelines;
* Lead expert session meeting and minute the meeting;
* Development of the capital models under Pillar 2 (asset, banking models, exchange rate, strategic risk, concentration risk);
* Development of the stress test models;
* Development of IRRBB models;
* Create model change calendar and manage model development projects;
* Develop models according to the internal development standards and in line with the model governance framework;
* Assess the compliancy of the models to the regulation and fill in the regulatory checklist;
* Assess the model risk and propose resolution to maintain the model risk within the model risk appetite;
* Estimate the impact of the model changes qualitative and quantitative;
* Peer review and quality assurance of developed models;
* Register and update the model in the model inventory.









**Model Governance:** 



* Register and update the model in the model inventory;
* Attest model in the model inventory;
* Update model observation when issue is resolved;
* Provide answers to validation questions;
* Provide answers to audit questions;
* Maintain the model standard for each model category (Asset Risk, IRRBB, Stress Test).









**Model Monitoring \& Implementation:** 



* Analyse the model monitoring reports and identify potential issues;
* Propose resolutions to model monitoring issues (e.g. model risk adjustment or redevelopment/calibration);
* Provide model implementation document;
* Provide data requirements for implementation;
* Ensure that model is implemented in line with the requirements;
* Support model user in case of unexplained trends in the model outcome.









**Maintenance of Models:** 



* Maintenance and 2nd line support of Pillar 2 \+ Stress;
* Ensure timely resolution of model observations (validation finding or monitoring finding);
* Ensure model validation findings are resolved within agreed timelines;
* Analyse the model monitoring reports and identify potential issues;
* Maintain model performance within the model risk appetite.









